---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BlogLikeButton from '../../components/BlogLikeButton.astro';
import BlogSubscribeCTA from '../../components/BlogSubscribeCTA.astro';

const keywords =
	'FHUGAWZ, dark pop, cinematic dark pop, independent artist, music production, artist branding, music and design, visual identity, Billie Eilish influence, Nirvana influence, Pierce the Veil, Sullii, Last Daybreak, Onyx band';
const excerpt =
	'A personal note on music, design, recovery and the long process of turning scattered influences into a dark pop world.';
---

<Layout
	title="Fhugawz — Why Fhugawz Exists"
	description="The story behind FHUGAWZ: from early bands, classical guitar, rock and metalcore influences to design, branding, music production and a cinematic dark pop project."
	spanishTitle="Por Qué Existe FHUGAWZ: Música, Diseño e Identidad Dark Pop | FHUGAWZ"
	spanishDescription="La historia detrás de FHUGAWZ: desde bandas, guitarra clásica, influencias de rock y metalcore hasta diseño, branding, producción musical y un proyecto dark pop cinematográfico."
	keywords={keywords}
	image="/images/blog/why-fhugawz-exists/why-fhugawz-exists-music-origin-hero.webp.webp"
>
	<section
		class="page-hero with-image blog-article-hero"
		style={`--page-hero-image: url("/images/blog/why-fhugawz-exists/why-fhugawz-exists-music-origin-hero.webp.webp")`}
	>
		<div class="site-shell">
			<p class="section-kicker" data-i18n="post.exists.kicker">PROJECT DIARY</p>
			<h1 class="page-title" data-i18n="post.exists.title">WHY FHUGAWZ EXISTS</h1>
			<p class="lede" data-i18n="post.exists.lede">{excerpt}</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="section">
		<article class="site-shell article">
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.intro.one">
				FHUGAWZ did not appear from one single decision. It is the result of years of music,
				distance, design, recovery and unfinished ideas that kept asking for a clearer form.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.intro.two">
				I started getting into music around 2005. At first, it was guitar, songs, bands and the
				need to understand why certain sounds could stay inside the body for years. During that
				time I studied classical guitar, played in different projects and slowly started building a
				personal relationship with music that was never only technical. It was always emotional
				first.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/why-fhugawz-exists/why-fhugawz-exists-classical-guitar-bands.webp"
					alt="Early musical origin and dark pop identity behind FHUGAWZ."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.exists.image.one.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.exists.music.heading">WHY MUSIC STAYED</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.music.one">
				Before FHUGAWZ, there were several bands and experiments. Some were practical: two cover
				bands created to play classic rock songs in English and native rock songs in bars and earn
				money through music. Others were more personal: an experimental project, a metalcore band,
				a pop rock band and several loose songs that did not belong to any fixed group.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.music.two">
				The two most important projects from that time were Last Daybreak, a metalcore band, and
				Onyx, a pop rock band. Both projects became serious attempts to build something scalable,
				rehearse consistently and understand what it means to defend original music over time.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a
					class="button primary article-soundcloud-button"
					href="https://soundcloud.com/jean-fh-gawz"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					data-i18n="post.exists.soundcloud"
				>
					LISTEN
				</a>
			</p>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.exists.image.heading">FROM SOUND TO IMAGE</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.image.one">
				Around 2015, design became another language. I started learning graphic design on my own
				and eventually used it as a way to work and make a living.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.image.two">
				That changed the way I understood music. A song was no longer only a song. It needed a
				visual world, a tone, a system, an atmosphere, a way of being presented. Later, I kept
				studying production, branding, product design and creative strategy through platforms like
				Platzi, Google and other learning spaces.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.image.three">
				Over time, the two worlds started connecting: music and design, sound and image, emotion
				and structure.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/why-fhugawz-exists/why-fhugawz-exists-design-branding-process.webp"
					alt="Design, branding and visual process connected to the FHUGAWZ project."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.exists.image.two.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.exists.return.heading">THE RETURN AFTER THE BREAK</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.return.one">
				After the personal incident described in the first AXIOMS article, returning to music felt
				different.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.return.two">
				This was not about making songs just to make songs. It was about building something with
				enough emotional weight, visual consistency and professional direction to carry everything
				that had happened. That process changed the purpose of the project.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a class="article-link" href="/blog/building-axioms" data-i18n="post.exists.firstArticle">
					Building AXIOMS
				</a>
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.return.three">
				The idea became clearer: even without ideal resources, perfect conditions or an easy path,
				it is possible to build something serious if the work is approached with discipline,
				patience and care.
			</p>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.exists.sound.heading">WHAT SHAPED THE SOUND</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.sound.one">
				FHUGAWZ also exists because the influences were never only from one place.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.sound.two">
				Nirvana shaped part of the raw emotional center. Secret &amp; Whisper brought another
				sense of intensity and atmosphere. Pierce the Veil opened a door to dramatic emotion and
				post-hardcore urgency. Sullii became an important reference during recovery, especially
				because of the way fragility and digital melancholy can coexist. Billie Eilish became one
				of the strongest references for how a modern pop project can be intimate, dark, minimal,
				visual and massive at the same time.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.sound.three">
				FHUGAWZ comes from that mix: rock energy, dark pop intimacy, cinematic atmosphere,
				digital texture, emotional writing and visual direction.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/why-fhugawz-exists/why-fhugawz-exists-dark-pop-creative-world.webp.webp"
					alt="Dark pop creative world combining music, image and production."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.exists.image.three.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.exists.now.heading">WHY IT EXISTS NOW</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.now.one">
				FHUGAWZ exists to prove that an artistic project can be built from fragments.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.now.two">
				From old bands. From design work. From recovery. From personal rupture. From references.
				From songs that never found their place before. From the need to create a professional
				world even when the starting point is imperfect.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.now.three">
				It is music, but it is also visual identity, production, storytelling and a way to turn
				difficult experiences into something structured enough to share.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.now.four">
				That is the reason FHUGAWZ exists: to build a dark pop world where sound, image and
				emotion do not feel separated.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.exists.closing">
				Follow the project, listen to the previews and stay close to the process. This is still
				being built.
			</p>

			<footer class="article-footer">
				<BlogLikeButton slug="why-fhugawz-exists" />
				<BlogSubscribeCTA id="why-fhugawz-exists-subscribe" />
			</footer>
		</article>
	</section>
</Layout>
